<paragraph id="932736CCFFB2FFAF3F99FFF0FB32FC4D" blockId="9.[151,1437,561,1056]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3F99FFF0FD18FD65" bold="true" box="[199,705,669,696]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">Justification of the transfer and synonymy.</emphasis>
This species possesses diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName id="54984D4FFFB2FFAF3BE5FFF3FAE8FD65" authorityName="Westring" authorityYear="1851" box="[1211,1329,670,696]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3BE5FFF3FAE8FD65" box="[1211,1329,670,696]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">Drassodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: trochanters notched, epigyne with curved lateral margins and vulva consists of primary and secondary spermathecae (compare 
<figureCitation id="0BA32A49FFB2FFAF3F90FF8BFE92FCDD" box="[206,331,742,768]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,187,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-27@10.[151,1436,181,1769]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 38–43. Drassodes luridus (O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1874), types of Megamyrmaekion kajalae Biswas &amp; Biswas, 1992. 38 holotype female habitus, dorsal view; 39 paratype female habitus, dorsal view; 40–41 genitalia of holotype female (40 epigyne, ventral view, 41 vulva, dorsal view); 42 epigyne of paratype female, ventral view; 43 label from type tube. Abbreviations: PS, primary spermatheca; SS, secondary spermatheca. Scale bars: 38–39, 2 mm; 40–42, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531783/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">Figs 40–42</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation id="F7094B3DFFB2FFAF3ED4FF8BFD47FCDD" author="Platnick, N. I. &amp; Shadab, M. U." box="[394,670,742,768]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" pagination="1 - 29" refId="ref10288" refString="Platnick, N. I. &amp; Shadab, M. U. (1976) A revision of the spider genera Drassodes and Tivodrassus (Araneae, Gnaphosidae) in North America. American Museum Novitates, 2593, 1 - 29." type="journal article" year="1976">Platnick &amp; Shadab 1976</bibRefCitation>
: figs 31–32, 35–36). Study of the 
<typeStatus id="4C23886EFFB2FFAF3B47FF8BFB8DFCDD" box="[1049,1108,742,768]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="54984D4FFFB2FFAF3B26FF8AFB36FCDD" authorityName="Biswas &amp; Biswas" authorityYear="1992" box="[1144,1263,742,768]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Megamyrmecion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kajalae">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3B26FF8AFB36FCDD" box="[1144,1263,742,768]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">M. kajalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it well fits to the diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName id="54984D4FFFB2FFAF3D0FFE66FD1BFCF9" authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1982" box="[593,706,778,804]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3D0FFE66FD1BFCF9" box="[593,706,778,804]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">D. luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: inverted pyriform epigynal plate with antero-laterally thickened rims and small, sclerotised, horizontally oriented primary spermathecae with large, hyaline, inflated balloon-like secondary spermathecae (compare 
<figureCitation id="0BA32A49FFB2FFAF3D7AFE3FFD7AFCB1" box="[548,675,850,876]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–43" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,187,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-27@10.[151,1436,181,1769]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 38–43. Drassodes luridus (O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1874), types of Megamyrmaekion kajalae Biswas &amp; Biswas, 1992. 38 holotype female habitus, dorsal view; 39 paratype female habitus, dorsal view; 40–41 genitalia of holotype female (40 epigyne, ventral view, 41 vulva, dorsal view); 42 epigyne of paratype female, ventral view; 43 label from type tube. Abbreviations: PS, primary spermatheca; SS, secondary spermatheca. Scale bars: 38–39, 2 mm; 40–42, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531783/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">Figs 40–42</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation id="F7094B3DFFB2FFAF3DBAFE3FFCA6FCB1" author="Tikader, B. K." box="[740,895,850,876]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" pagination="295 - 536" refId="ref10742" refString="Tikader, B. K. (1982). Part 2. Family Gnaphosidae. In: The fauna of India. Spiders: Araneae. Vol. II. Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta, pp. 295 - 536." type="book chapter" year="1982">Tikader 1982</bibRefCitation>
: figs 261–262 and 
<bibRefCitation id="F7094B3DFFB2FFAF3B06FE3FFAF9FCB1" author="Caleb, J. T. D. &amp; Karthikeyani, R. &amp; Muthuchelian, K." box="[1112,1312,850,876]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" pagination="135 - 138" refId="ref9568" refString="Caleb, J. T. D., Karthikeyani, R. &amp; Muthuchelian, K. (2014) Description of Drassodes luridus O. P. Cambridge (Araneae: Gnaphosidae): First record from Tamil Nadu, India. Journal of Entomology and Zoology Studies, 2, 135 - 138." type="journal article" year="2014">
Caleb 
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3BFCFE3EFB05FCB1" box="[1186,1244,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1e–f). Based on these observations, we propose to consider 
<taxonomicName id="54984D4FFFB2FFAF3DB2FE1AFCBAFC4D" authorityName="Biswas &amp; Biswas" authorityYear="1992" box="[748,867,886,912]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Megamyrmecion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kajalae">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3DB2FE1AFCBAFC4D" box="[748,867,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">M. kajalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="54984D4FFFB2FFAF3B2CFE1AFB3AFC4D" authorityName="Tikader" authorityYear="1982" box="[1138,1251,886,912]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3B2CFE1AFB3AFC4D" box="[1138,1251,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">D. luridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DB826547FFB2FFAF3F99FEF7FB56FBFD" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="932736CCFFB2FFAF3F99FEF7FB56FBFD" blockId="9.[151,1437,561,1056]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3F99FEF7FEE2FC69" bold="true" box="[199,315,922,948]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">Remarks.</emphasis>
The ZSI collection has two glass tubes with ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="54984D4FFFB2FFAF3C14FEF6FC1AFC69" authorityName="Biswas &amp; Biswas" authorityYear="1992" box="[842,963,922,948]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Megamyrmecion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kajalae">
<emphasis id="A1ECEADEFFB2FFAF3C14FEF6FC1AFC69" box="[842,963,922,948]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">M. kajalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’. There is a common label for both these tubes that mentions as ‘ 
<typeStatus id="4C23886EFFB2FFAF3EFEFED3FDDEFC05" box="[416,519,958,984]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548">holotype</typeStatus>
and paratype’ with registration numbers ‘5408/18’ and ‘5409/18’ respectively. A tube contains 
<specimenCount id="859EFD45FFB2FFAF3E6CFE8FFE77FC21" box="[306,430,994,1020]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen in good condition. The same tube has a micro-vial containing the dissected epigyne. The other tube contains 
<specimenCount id="859EFD45FFB2FFAF3EB4F96BFDBCFBFD" box="[490,613,1030,1056]" pageId="9" pageNumber="548" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen in good condition, with intact epigyne.
</paragraph>
